OL,6,F"As I walked round the corner I could
OL,7,Fnot believe the devastation, it was
OL,8,Fjust a sea of filth." said Mr Cornock.
OL,10,FThe law says that it is the
OL,11,Flandowner's responsibility to dispose
OL,12,Fof the rubbish left by fly-tippers.
OL,13,FHattie Severinsen, from the National
OL,14,FFarmers' Union (NFU), believes farmers
OL,15,Fshould not be left to clean up the
OL,16,Fmess.
OL,18,FShe said: "Fly-tipping is a huge issue
OL,19,Ffor farmers and it should not be there
OL,20,Fresponsibility to prevent it.
