OL,3,CFly-tipping 'tidal wave' as councils
OL,4,Cstruggle to prosecute perpetrators
OL,6,FIn South Gloucestershire last year
OL,7,Fonly 1% of the 1800 incidents were
OL,8,Fprosecuted, although the council says
OL,9,Fit did successfully track down repeat
OL,10,Foffenders. It adds there are huge
OL,11,Fchallenges in rural areas with a lack
OL,12,Fof CCTV and witnesses.
OL,14,FSouth Gloucestershire Council says:
OL,15,F"Fly-tipping is completely
OL,16,Funacceptable and can blight local
OL,17,Fcommunities and the countryside,
OL,18,Fcausing an environmental hazard and
OL,19,Fharming nature.
