OL,3,CFly-tipping 'tidal wave' as councils
OL,4,Cstruggle to prosecute perpetrators
OL,6,F"Although it is the landowner's
OL,7,Fresponsibility to clear fly-tipped
OL,8,Fwaste from private land, we
OL,9,Finvestigate these incidents and do our
OL,10,Fbest to recover compensation through
OL,11,Fthe courts if a perpetrator is
OL,12,Fprosecuted as a result.
OL,14,F"Our advice to farmers and other
OL,15,Fprivate landowners is to remain
OL,16,Fvigilant and report any suspicious
OL,17,Factivity to the Police. We also advise
OL,18,Fthem to do their best to ensure their
OL,19,Fland is secure so only those with
OL,20,Fpermission can gain access."
